cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV

This paper deals with natural language processing and parsing, specifically focusing on the issue of sentences with gapping. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses methods for parsing and reconstructing elided material, which could fall under sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions downstream natural language understanding tasks, which could relate to sub-categories such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
